17:11.431 --> 17:13.498
     And from now on you
     do what you're told.

17:14.733 --> 17:16.733
          (slamming)

17:16.736 --> 17:19.537
- [Charlotte Voiceover] I guess
  most things die painfully.

17:20.607 --> 17:22.607
 It doesn't seem fair that the
  last few minutes you've got

17:22.608 --> 17:26.377
  are probably filled with
  terror, pain, or sadness.

17:26.378 --> 17:29.614
     ("Follow Me" by Batz)

17:33.453 --> 17:34.452
You go through your whole life

17:34.454 --> 17:36.621
trying to avoid those feelings.

17:38.491 --> 17:40.825
     Then suddenly there's
    a bullet in your chest.

17:42.362 --> 17:43.661
 Or you're being eaten alive.

17:49.069 --> 17:50.252
        - It says that

17:50.253 --> 17:51.436
   two people checked in the
       Shacks that night.

17:51.438 --> 17:52.703
 Steve Linder and Jesse Atlas.

17:52.705 --> 17:54.405
 Your name's not even on here!

17:56.810 --> 17:58.242
             - Oh.

17:58.244 --> 18:00.278
     I wasn't gonna check
    in under my real name.

18:01.347 --> 18:02.747
       I booked in under
     the name Jesse Atlas.

18:02.749 --> 18:05.516
  I just took it from that
  day's newspaper headline.

18:07.687 --> 18:09.420
      - [Charlotte] What
      was the headline?

18:09.422 --> 18:11.656
     - [Max] Some kind of
    tragedy from that day.

18:13.159 --> 18:15.293
  Maybe a boat accident or--

18:15.295 --> 18:16.494
        - Shark attack.

18:16.496 --> 18:19.397
      (perplexed music)

18:26.739 --> 18:29.240
          (slamming)

18:30.510 --> 18:32.877
         (eerie music)

18:41.387 --> 18:43.855
        (fan rattling)

18:50.897 --> 18:52.663
      Dad wanted me to
      give this to you.

18:58.371 --> 18:59.270
          It's good.

19:01.674 --> 19:03.574
 - [Edmund Voiceover] Catching
 a criminal can be difficult,

19:03.576 --> 19:05.543
  but it's never impressive.

19:05.545 --> 19:06.878
 I mean, who caught Ted Bundy?

19:06.880 --> 19:08.613
      Who caught fucking
       John Wayne Gacy?

19:08.615 --> 19:09.714
      Who gives a shit?

19:09.716 --> 19:11.682
- Hey sweetie, we have a guest.

19:11.684 --> 19:12.817
  Put some coffee in the pot.

19:12.819 --> 19:13.751
     - [Edmund Voiceover]
         Ask any cop.

19:13.753 --> 19:14.752
  You've forgotten in a week.

19:14.754 --> 19:15.753
      - [Edmund] Come in.

19:16.856 --> 19:18.289
     - Detective Sophia--

19:18.291 --> 19:19.357
  - Yeah, I know who you are.

19:20.560 --> 19:21.893
- [Sophia] Inspirational story.

19:21.895 --> 19:23.594
Unfortunate victim standing up

19:23.596 --> 19:24.729
against the lazy incompetent--

19:24.731 --> 19:25.663
- [Edmund] No, you misread it.

19:25.665 --> 19:27.465
  It didn't say standing up.

19:27.467 --> 19:29.600
 - [Sophia] Sorry, rising up.

19:29.602 --> 19:30.434
     - [Edmund Voiceover]
    What you want to catch

19:30.436 --> 19:31.636
    is people's attention.

19:32.472 --> 19:34.605
  A premonition or a vision,

19:34.607 --> 19:35.840
            a dream.

19:35.842 --> 19:37.441
 People listen to that stuff.

19:37.443 --> 19:39.877
    They don't necessarily
 believe it, but they like it.

19:41.281 --> 19:42.246
  - [Charlotte Voiceover] He
   knew there'd be no point

19:42.248 --> 19:43.514
    catching Max on his own.

19:44.751 --> 19:47.685
  People would always sooner
    believe mum over him,

19:47.687 --> 19:49.420
     even if she was dead.

19:49.422 --> 19:50.555
      - [Sophia] Sophia.

19:50.557 --> 19:52.423
    - [Charlotte] Charlotte.

19:52.425 --> 19:54.759
     - Hey, did you enjoy
     the Maritime Festival

19:54.761 --> 19:56.394
        the other night?

19:56.396 --> 19:57.595
            - Sorry?

19:57.597 --> 19:58.930
        - Opening night.

19:58.932 --> 20:01.599
    You were watching the
  fireworks near the docks.

20:01.601 --> 20:04.702
    You were wearing a blue
  cardigan over a pink dress.

20:04.704 --> 20:07.371
     But you had different
     hair, short and dark.

20:07.373 --> 20:09.207
     - No, that wasn't me.

20:09.209 --> 20:10.641
    I stayed home all night.

20:11.744 --> 20:13.878
   - [Edmund Voiceover] Too
 many facts obscure the truth.

20:13.880 --> 20:16.247
      Most cases are so
       fucking boring.

20:16.249 --> 20:18.282
      A confession or a
      witness account.

20:18.284 --> 20:20.685
It's just forgettable bullshit.

20:20.687 --> 20:22.587
People prefer a bit of darkness.

20:24.724 --> 20:27.758
        (ethereal music)

20:30.630 --> 20:32.697
    - [Edmund] You suddenly
     fit the description.

20:34.834 --> 20:35.833
      Wouldn't you agree?

20:38.871 --> 20:39.770
            - Yes.

20:39.772 --> 20:42.840
      (dreamlike music)

20:43.776 --> 20:45.576
     - [Edmund] These are
    your mother's clothes.

20:48.881 --> 20:49.880
          Disgusting.

20:52.919 --> 20:54.785
     So, how do you plead?

20:58.458 --> 20:59.323
          - Guilty.

21:01.027 --> 21:01.993
    - [Edmund] I thought so.

21:01.995 --> 21:04.996
      (bewitching music)

21:08.501 --> 21:09.533
         - I'm sorry.

21:09.535 --> 21:11.669
      (twinkling music)

21:16.042 --> 21:18.809
- [Edmund] Not yet you're not.

21:20.713 --> 21:22.847
       If you refuse to
     stay in bed at night,

21:24.917 --> 21:27.018
        the punishment
      will fit the crime.

21:27.020 --> 21:29.820
        (troubled music)

21:42.702 --> 21:43.934
   - [Charlotte Voiceover]
There's this place I try to go

21:43.936 --> 21:45.536
  when I can't get to sleep.

21:46.873 --> 21:48.906
         (Max grunts)

21:48.908 --> 21:50.341
     It's nothing special.

21:51.811 --> 21:54.679
      (celestial music)

21:56.749 --> 21:59.884
It's just flat earth stretching
     on forever around me.

21:59.886 --> 22:02.620
        (fan whirring)

22:03.856 --> 22:06.657
        (dreadful music)

22:15.868 --> 22:17.401
      No one can see me.

22:20.740 --> 22:22.440
     Nothing can touch me.

22:22.442 --> 22:25.543
        (woman laughing)

22:25.545 --> 22:27.611
        (woman moaning)

22:27.613 --> 22:29.747
     (electronic whirring)

22:29.749 --> 22:30.815
      (car horn honking)

22:30.817 --> 22:33.851
(people chattering and laughing)

22:33.853 --> 22:36.420
         (eerie music)

22:45.131 --> 22:48.032
      (woman screaming)

22:52.939 --> 22:55.773
        (fiery rumbling)

22:55.775 --> 22:57.775
     Dad said the necklace
     needed to look rusted

22:57.777 --> 22:59.677
for the reporter and the cops.

23:01.147 --> 23:03.781
It upset me to see it that way.

23:03.783 --> 23:05.983
    Especially since we'd
  only just gotten it back.

23:07.520 --> 23:10.388
   - I try and remember more
about what happened that night,

23:10.390 --> 23:13.557
      and I figure if he
     ran in this direction

23:13.559 --> 23:14.925
  from where he left his car,

23:16.429 --> 23:19.930
  it's possible he would've
     hit this road here.

23:23.035 --> 23:25.603
 And the time that it took him
  from where he left the car

23:25.605 --> 23:28.406
     means he would've got
    there around 11:00 p.m.

23:28.408 --> 23:31.675
      Now, this is where
       it gets spooky.

23:32.779 --> 23:34.812
      I had a dream last
     night with Juliette.

23:35.848 --> 23:37.681
 I'm sitting out by the pool,

23:37.683 --> 23:39.917
     and she's got these
    cards in front of her.

23:39.919 --> 23:42.186
She turns over the first card.

23:42.188 --> 23:44.889
There's a picture of a pendant.

23:44.891 --> 23:47.925
    Thing is, it's the same
    pendant she was wearing

23:47.927 --> 23:49.627
  the night she was killed,

23:49.629 --> 23:51.996
    the very same pendant
  that was reported missing

23:51.998 --> 23:54.632
     from the hit-and-run
     scene six years ago.

23:54.634 --> 23:55.499
  - [Joe] That's very weird.

23:55.501 --> 23:56.700
    - Well it gets weirder.

23:56.702 --> 23:58.936
 She turns over the next card.

23:58.938 --> 24:01.539
     There's a picture of
     a Great White shark.

24:01.541 --> 24:03.040
 And I look out into the pool,

24:03.042 --> 24:04.975
      the fucking thing's
         in the water!

24:06.012 --> 24:07.812
        So next day, I
      start checking down

24:07.814 --> 24:09.613
     some of these motels
        and roadhouses

24:09.615 --> 24:10.815
  along this stretch of road

24:10.817 --> 24:12.183
to try and get records of anyone

24:12.185 --> 24:13.884
that booked in late that night.

24:13.886 --> 24:15.152
      And there was one.

24:15.154 --> 24:17.588
        In a place that
      rents beach shacks.

24:19.091 --> 24:22.927
      Now, you ever heard
        of Jesse Atlas?

24:22.929 --> 24:24.161
             - No.

24:24.163 --> 24:25.229
    - Well the poor son of
     a bitch was attacked

24:25.231 --> 24:26.997
 and killed by a Great White,

24:26.999 --> 24:28.632
        bitten in half,

24:28.634 --> 24:31.569
 the very day before Juliette
  and I were hit by the car.

24:32.738 --> 24:33.671
 - It's very strange, and all,

24:33.673 --> 24:34.872
but I don't see as any relevance

24:34.874 --> 24:36.474
to what we're talking about now.

24:36.476 --> 24:38.042
  - Well Joe, it just seems
  that it would've been hard

24:38.044 --> 24:40.211
     for him to have booked
    into a motel that night,

24:40.213 --> 24:41.679
          that's all,

24:41.681 --> 24:44.081
      especially being in
      two fucking pieces!

24:45.218 --> 24:47.251
  Someone was booked in under
    a fake name that night,

24:47.253 --> 24:50.054
     that they lifted from
     that day's headline!

24:50.056 --> 24:53.123
        (creepy music)

24:53.125 --> 24:55.960
        (fan rattling)

25:05.271 --> 25:06.203
        Exercise time.

25:07.540 --> 25:08.272
      - [Woman On Radio]
        Coming up next

25:08.274 --> 25:10.074
 we have a very special guest

25:10.076 --> 25:12.643
        who just had a
      very special gift.

25:12.645 --> 25:14.945
          (splashing)

25:14.947 --> 25:17.047
        (heavenly music)

25:17.049 --> 25:21.652
      (voices chattering
       over each other)

25:33.666 --> 25:35.666
    - [Max Voiceover] Edmund
      was totally insane,

25:35.668 --> 25:37.067
  but he wasn't a total fool.

25:38.104 --> 25:39.603
        He had a plan.

25:39.605 --> 25:41.939
       - Now let's get
     this story straight.

25:41.941 --> 25:43.307
When you arrived at the motel,

25:43.309 --> 25:45.776
  you accidentally drop the
   pendant down the drain.

25:45.778 --> 25:47.077
  - [Max Voiceover] And it
  wasn't just this bullshit

25:47.079 --> 25:49.113
      about Juliette and
       the tarot cards.

25:49.115 --> 25:50.114
    That was the sideshow.

25:51.617 --> 25:54.118
    Carnie showmanship for
    the psychic TV crowd.

25:56.022 --> 25:57.655
 The real stuff would be found

25:57.657 --> 25:59.023
 in the book he was going to
release after I'd been caught,

25:59.025 --> 26:01.091
      which would explain
     how he really did it.

26:02.828 --> 26:05.896
    Precise detective work
    and endless research.

26:06.999 --> 26:10.100
     Which of course would
    also be total bullshit.

26:10.102 --> 26:11.669
  And what does that matter?

26:13.105 --> 26:14.705
      He had me to help
      him bend the truth

26:14.707 --> 26:16.106
  whichever way he saw fit.

26:17.310 --> 26:18.976
  People could put holes in
  their stories and evidence

26:18.978 --> 26:20.077
        all they liked,

26:20.079 --> 26:22.012
but as long as I was in of it,

26:22.014 --> 26:24.748
    no one would ever know
  for certain how he did it.

26:26.886 --> 26:29.286
  - [Charlotte Voiceover] As
ridiculous as dad's story was,

26:29.288 --> 26:31.889
  it only seemed a fraction
    worse than the truth.

26:35.828 --> 26:37.761
Max had barely hidden his car.

26:37.763 --> 26:40.097
He'd obviously faked his name.

26:40.099 --> 26:42.099
  He kept the number plates.

26:42.101 --> 26:43.200
     He kept the necklace.

26:46.105 --> 26:49.006
    Yet somehow, until he
    showed up at our door,

26:49.008 --> 26:50.908
  not a soul knew he did it.

26:53.012 --> 26:56.113
    It was as if he hadn't
     been running at all,

26:56.115 --> 26:57.147
         just waiting.

26:57.917 --> 26:59.683
     Waiting to be caught.

26:59.685 --> 27:01.385
    Waiting to be punished.

27:01.387 --> 27:03.621
        (fan rattling)

27:03.623 --> 27:06.256
        (feverish music)

27:12.632 --> 27:15.633
      (electric zapping)

27:22.808 --> 27:23.707
            - Fuck.

27:30.850 --> 27:33.684
        (sonic rumbling)

27:45.831 --> 27:48.899
      (ghostly breathing)

27:54.340 --> 27:55.906
          (splashing)

27:55.908 --> 27:58.442
        (elegant music)

28:20.032 --> 28:23.767
  (moves into dreadful music)

28:29.108 --> 28:32.042
        (fiery roaring)

28:35.147 --> 28:37.881
     - You've captured it.
        - Captured it.

28:37.883 --> 28:40.184
      - You can kill him.
      - Waiting for you.

28:40.186 --> 28:41.719
     - [Female Voiceover]
     You've captured it.

28:41.721 --> 28:45.923
     - [Female Voiceover] I
    don't deserve it though.

28:45.925 --> 28:47.091
  (female voices whispering)

28:47.093 --> 28:49.860
      (heavy breathing)

28:49.862 --> 28:52.229
         (crazy music)

30:23.222 --> 30:25.989
  - What are your thoughts?

30:25.991 --> 30:27.224
        - Hard to say.

30:28.294 --> 30:29.560
 Might've been six years ago,

30:29.562 --> 30:31.528
    but this place feels
  like he's only just left.

30:31.530 --> 30:34.498
      (suspicious music)

30:38.337 --> 30:39.303
    - [Charlotte Voiceover]
     There was a new story

30:39.305 --> 30:40.971
about what happened that night.

30:40.973 --> 30:43.907
- If you'd just killed someone
 and horribly maimed another,

30:43.909 --> 30:45.275
what would you do when you go?

30:45.277 --> 30:46.944
   - [Charlotte Voiceover]
  This time when Max arrived

30:46.946 --> 30:49.012
 at the motel he accidentally
    dropped mum's necklace

30:49.014 --> 30:50.080
        down the sink.

30:50.082 --> 30:52.416
         (scary music)

30:58.290 --> 31:00.123
    On the same day dad was
     showing the reporter

31:00.125 --> 31:01.491
    where mom's pendant was,

31:01.493 --> 31:02.960
      a girl I used to
      go to school with

31:02.962 --> 31:05.295
    had been found stabbed
    to death in her home.

31:06.465 --> 31:08.565
    They caught the killer
      in an old factory.

31:10.336 --> 31:12.236
      He shared the place
    with the body of a girl

31:12.238 --> 31:14.404
      who went missing up
     north five years ago.

31:15.274 --> 31:17.641
        Or what was left
        of her, I guess.

31:19.211 --> 31:21.078
 - [Woman In Movie] She looks
  so strange, with her eyes.

31:21.614 --> 31:23.380
  - [Charlotte Voiceover] Dad
   was still the front page.

31:23.382 --> 31:27.317
  ("Sid and Nancy" by Batz)

31:27.319 --> 31:29.519
- Any searching that room yet?

31:29.521 --> 31:32.222
      - Uh, we'll be out
      of your hair soon.

31:32.224 --> 31:33.123
            So um,

31:34.260 --> 31:35.459
you haven't remembered anymore

31:35.461 --> 31:37.961
    about the man who booked
      in here that night?

31:37.963 --> 31:39.997
      - Only what I told
       the other cops.

31:39.999 --> 31:42.132
     He called complaining
     about his television,

31:42.134 --> 31:43.500
      said it was broken.

31:43.502 --> 31:45.402
  - [Sophia] Which it wasn't.

31:45.404 --> 31:46.970
        - That's right.

31:46.972 --> 31:48.405
When we checked it, it was fine.

31:51.210 --> 31:52.175
- [Sophia] And you describe him

31:52.177 --> 31:53.677
  as an unassuming young man.

31:53.679 --> 31:55.412
     Are you sure you can't
    remember anymore details

31:55.414 --> 31:56.446
  about what he looked like?

31:56.448 --> 31:57.414
    - It was six years ago!

31:58.984 --> 32:00.384
    Look, he didn't have a
  swastika between his eyes,

32:00.386 --> 32:02.352
    if you know what I mean.

32:02.354 --> 32:03.654
      - [Sophia] What are
       you doing there?

32:04.590 --> 32:06.556
      - Scratch and win.

32:06.558 --> 32:09.493
     - Are you sure you're
     not just scratching?

32:09.495 --> 32:11.461
  - Gotta be in it to win it.

32:11.463 --> 32:12.429
      - What do you win?

32:14.333 --> 32:15.465
      - A million bones.

32:16.969 --> 32:18.135
          A big boat.

32:18.137 --> 32:19.469
        Home makeover.

32:19.471 --> 32:21.638
 You know, all kinds of stuff.

32:21.640 --> 32:23.106
            - Yeah?

32:23.108 --> 32:24.374
     Well what will you do
     if you win the money?

32:24.376 --> 32:25.542
 - I'll fucking give it away,

32:25.544 --> 32:26.410
          to charity.

32:26.412 --> 32:27.511
             - Mm.

32:29.248 --> 32:30.180
    Well that's really nice.

32:30.182 --> 32:31.281
             - Mm.

32:31.283 --> 32:34.084
      - Good, good idea.
           - Mm-hm.

32:36.689 --> 32:39.489
- [Edmund] So what did you do
when you left the beach shack?

32:39.491 --> 32:41.258
       - [Max] I caught
      a bus the next day

32:42.061 --> 32:43.026
      and I headed home.

32:44.029 --> 32:45.028
      - [Edmund] A bus?

32:45.030 --> 32:46.463
         - [Max] Yeah.

32:46.465 --> 32:48.231
        - Were you gonna
        hide the plates?

32:48.233 --> 32:49.967
  - Yeah, it crossed my mind.

32:49.969 --> 32:51.501
        - Whereabouts?

32:51.503 --> 32:52.336
          - The Sun.

32:52.338 --> 32:53.570
            - Sorry?

32:53.572 --> 32:55.072
          - The Sun.

32:55.074 --> 32:57.007
     It's an old mineshaft
     just outside of town.

32:57.676 --> 33:01.111
    (knocking on the door)

33:03.082 --> 33:04.514
       - [Sophia] Oh, hi
    Charlotte, how's things?

33:04.516 --> 33:05.482
        - Hi, uh, great.

33:05.484 --> 33:06.717
         How are you?

33:06.719 --> 33:07.517
     - [Sophia] I'm a bit
      stressed actually.

33:07.519 --> 33:09.152
      Is your dad about?

33:09.154 --> 33:11.088
  - Uh, he's, he's actually
     busy at the moment.

33:11.089 --> 33:13.023
  - [Sophia] Yeah, well look,
   I really need to see him.

33:13.025 --> 33:14.691
     - Um, I'll find him.

33:14.693 --> 33:16.226
  Um, I'll get him for you.

33:16.228 --> 33:18.362
      - [Sophia] Oh, no,
     look, I'll find him.

33:18.364 --> 33:20.430
      - It fits together
     like a fucking watch.

33:23.102 --> 33:25.469
        ¶ Pray for me ¶

33:30.275 --> 33:32.642
     - Detective Valmont,
     what brings you here?

33:34.513 --> 33:36.246
 - Our cream of the crop here.

33:36.248 --> 33:37.447
  - [Edmund] Uh, Charlotte,
      could you please

33:37.449 --> 33:39.082
      show the detective
    back inside the house,

33:39.084 --> 33:41.318
and I will meet with her when
I've got sufficient Vitamin D.

33:44.123 --> 33:45.722
        - With all due
      respect, Mr. Bloom,

33:45.724 --> 33:47.591
    you're going to have to
     surrender the pendant

33:47.593 --> 33:49.793
 or it's withholding evidence.

33:49.795 --> 33:50.761
            - Hey.

33:50.763 --> 33:52.195
    My stuff is your stuff.

33:54.800 --> 33:56.299
      Look, can we please
        talk about this

33:56.301 --> 33:58.235
  somewhere more appropriate?

33:58.237 --> 33:59.770
  Inside my own house maybe?

33:59.772 --> 34:02.606
        (strange music)

34:24.429 --> 34:25.795
     - [Sophia] Your wife
     was very beautiful.

34:25.797 --> 34:28.364
        - Never heard a
      bad word about her.

34:28.367 --> 34:30.634
 - [Sophia] People didn't like
 you so much though, did they?

34:30.636 --> 34:31.568
         - Come again?

34:31.570 --> 34:33.235
- People, they didn't like you.

34:33.237 --> 34:34.638
      - [Woman Voiceover]
       Hold your breath.

34:34.639 --> 34:35.472
      - [Woman Voiceover]
       Hold your breath.

34:35.474 --> 34:37.007
        (woman gasping)

34:37.007 --> 34:38.541
      - [Woman Voiceover]
       Dive in, dive in.

