    - Yeah, you should try
    getting hit by a car.

37:59.478 --> 38:00.744
    It's a fucking marathon.

38:01.947 --> 38:04.314
     I would've killed for
     the pain to go away.

38:06.485 --> 38:07.917
Until I couldn't feel my legs.

38:09.054 --> 38:10.987
      Now I'd kill for it
      to come back again.

38:15.794 --> 38:16.960
          Look, Max,

38:17.829 --> 38:20.297
        I'm sorry I made
        that joke, okay?

38:20.299 --> 38:21.798
     I do that sometimes.

38:21.800 --> 38:24.801
It's just my way of, you know,
 dealing with what happened.

38:24.803 --> 38:26.469
       Paramedics do the
     same thing, you know,

38:26.471 --> 38:27.804
    to help with the horror.

38:29.875 --> 38:31.641
      - [Max] Yeah, well
       whatever works.

38:33.912 --> 38:34.811
            - Yeah.

38:35.981 --> 38:36.846
             Well.

38:37.849 --> 38:38.948
        I'm off to bed.

38:40.819 --> 38:41.985
  I'll see you in the spring.

38:45.324 --> 38:46.856
      Max said he almost
        drowned today.

38:49.061 --> 38:50.060
      You saved his life.

38:52.364 --> 38:53.563
     - I almost left him.

38:55.701 --> 38:57.767
  - [Edmund] I would've been
very angry if you'd done that.

38:59.771 --> 39:02.405
   After all, he's almost as
innocent as me and your mother.

39:03.875 --> 39:06.076
 He didn't know what happened
    any more than we did.

39:07.779 --> 39:10.013
  He tried to get away with
    it, but he manned up.

39:10.015 --> 39:10.947
        He came clean.

39:10.949 --> 39:13.950
        (mystical music)

39:15.454 --> 39:16.353
             Now.

39:18.457 --> 39:19.823
    Listen to me carefully.

39:19.825 --> 39:22.559
        (totemic music)

39:24.429 --> 39:27.697
  Tomorrow you take Max back
    to where he came from.

39:27.699 --> 39:30.667
      (spell-like music)

39:38.043 --> 39:40.577
    I want you to follow him
     to a mineshaft nearby

39:40.579 --> 39:41.644
        called The Sun.

39:41.646 --> 39:44.814
     (mythological music)

39:45.984 --> 39:48.518
    Don't be seen by anyone.

39:48.520 --> 39:49.886
    And when you get there,

39:49.888 --> 39:51.921
 you make sure he does exactly

39:52.891 --> 39:53.857
    what he's supposed to.

39:56.928 --> 39:58.461
  We're getting closer now.

40:01.600 --> 40:03.600
        The last clue's
      been set in motion.

40:03.602 --> 40:06.403
        (hypnotic music)

40:08.140 --> 40:09.939
People are starting to listen.

40:10.909 --> 40:14.043
        (fire whooshing)

40:14.045 --> 40:16.913
Soon, they'll start to wonder.

40:16.915 --> 40:19.749
        (mystical music)

40:24.890 --> 40:27.023
          (rumbling)

40:34.666 --> 40:35.865
          (zapping)

40:40.705 --> 40:42.705
      - [Charlotte] What
     about that detective?

40:42.707 --> 40:45.575
      (perplexed music)

40:48.980 --> 40:51.181
   I'm just worried that she
 might start to figure it out.

40:51.183 --> 40:54.017
        (sneaky music)

40:57.088 --> 40:58.988
    - Don't worry about her.

40:58.990 --> 41:01.858
She wouldn't be able to figure
   out a fucking egg timer.

41:04.963 --> 41:06.729
     Now even though you
    don't deserve a reward

41:06.731 --> 41:08.031
        for saving Max,

41:09.968 --> 41:10.934
        I'll allow it.

41:14.005 --> 41:15.171
- Can I have my pictures back?

41:15.173 --> 41:16.072
             - No.

41:17.576 --> 41:19.742
     You've well and truly
     lost that privilege.

41:23.048 --> 41:24.981
    Because you did so well,

41:27.018 --> 41:27.984
    something even better.

41:29.921 --> 41:31.821
       You get to sleep
      in my bed tonight.

41:31.823 --> 41:34.624
        (haunting music)

41:36.962 --> 41:38.495
    - [Charlotte Voiceover]
        Mum used to run

41:38.497 --> 41:40.096
a charity modeling competition
    for the girls in town.

41:41.666 --> 41:44.067
   Somehow dad's story had
  made her seem alive again

41:44.069 --> 41:45.535
    and him seem tolerable.

41:47.739 --> 41:50.106
  They asked dad to present
    the winner that year.

41:51.076 --> 41:52.108
They'd never done that before.

41:52.110 --> 41:55.912
     (audience applauding)

41:55.914 --> 41:57.113
      - Thanks, everyone.

41:58.550 --> 42:00.884
    Thank you all for the
 support that you've given me

42:00.886 --> 42:02.185
 during these difficult times.

42:03.889 --> 42:06.289
      I just hope that I
     can prove to you all

42:06.291 --> 42:09.058
  that justice is something
     worth fighting for.

42:09.961 --> 42:11.978
    And whether you believe

42:11.979 --> 42:13.996
     Juliette's helping me
    solve this crime or not,

42:13.999 --> 42:17.200
    just remember, love is
     stronger than death.

42:17.202 --> 42:21.037
  ("Racketeer" by Pow Negro)

42:21.039 --> 42:23.006
Myth is stronger than history.

42:24.976 --> 42:28.044
  Hope is stronger than fear.

42:30.582 --> 42:33.182
      Wisdom is stronger
       than ignorance.

42:36.121 --> 42:36.986
          And dreams,

42:40.058 --> 42:43.259
      dreams are stronger
         than reality.

42:45.830 --> 42:48.264
 Whatever that means. (laughs)

42:49.568 --> 42:51.100
            Anyway,

42:51.102 --> 42:52.035
        tonight's winner

42:53.104 --> 42:54.070
             is...

42:54.072 --> 42:56.773
        (strange music)

42:58.610 --> 43:02.278
(audience applauds and cheers)

43:03.915 --> 43:06.716
        (balls clacking)

43:12.757 --> 43:13.890
          (banging)

43:13.892 --> 43:15.124
          (rumbling)

43:15.126 --> 43:16.159
        (siren wailing)

43:16.161 --> 43:19.112
      (car horn honking)

43:19.113 --> 43:22.064
       (tires squealing)
     (Charlotte cries out)

43:22.601 --> 43:25.068
         (phone rings)

43:27.672 --> 43:29.072
  - [Edmund] Where are you?

43:29.074 --> 43:30.006
      - I'm heading home.

43:30.008 --> 43:31.107
We just dropped off the plates.

43:31.109 --> 43:32.275
        - Where's Max?

43:32.277 --> 43:33.209
        - [Charlotte] I
     dropped him at a pub.

43:33.211 --> 43:34.911
- Turn around and pick him up.

43:34.913 --> 43:35.845
  - [Charlotte] But you said
 I couldn't be seen with him.

43:35.847 --> 43:37.046
  - I don't care what I said!

43:37.048 --> 43:38.214
        Pick him up and
      bring him home now!

43:42.921 --> 43:46.356
  ("Gameshow Queen" by Batz)

43:48.026 --> 43:51.227
      (thunder rumbling)

43:59.070 --> 44:00.770
     - Maxie, sweetheart!

44:00.772 --> 44:01.404
        Give us a kiss!

44:03.341 --> 44:05.141
I haven't seen you for a while.

44:05.143 --> 44:07.343
        Where have you
      been, on holidays?

44:07.345 --> 44:08.778
    Well, guess that means

44:08.780 --> 44:09.979
     you haven't needed any
    money recently. (laughs)

44:09.981 --> 44:10.880
        - Three years.

44:15.120 --> 44:17.887
      I haven't seen you
       for three years.

44:17.889 --> 44:20.189
      - Well honey, you
      are over 25 now.

44:21.126 --> 44:22.291
    What are you back for?

44:24.796 --> 44:25.995
      It's not to move
      back home, is it?

44:25.997 --> 44:27.997
        Because I don't
      live there anymore.

44:27.999 --> 44:29.232
    I found some somebody.

44:29.234 --> 44:31.901
     He sells jet-skis, you
      know, really light.

44:31.903 --> 44:33.670
        - Some stuff's
    happened recently, mum.

44:35.874 --> 44:36.839
      - What's happened?

44:38.943 --> 44:40.209
     - Stuff that's made
    me want to talk to you

44:40.211 --> 44:41.377
      about a few things.

44:43.348 --> 44:44.781
        - What things?

44:45.684 --> 44:46.382
          - Like me.

44:48.920 --> 44:51.020
    And about the way that
      you treated Mason.

44:51.856 --> 44:52.755
        - [June] Mason?

44:56.194 --> 44:58.795
    - The way that you left
     me to look after him.

44:58.797 --> 45:01.097
          (banging)

45:01.099 --> 45:03.232
 To look after him by myself.

45:06.304 --> 45:07.203
         Wasn't right.

45:09.274 --> 45:12.208
It was the one time you needed
 to step up, and you didn't.

45:12.210 --> 45:17.013
      ¶ Gameshow queen ¶

45:17.015 --> 45:22.118
  ¶ Everybody knows you're a
  gameshow gameshow queen ¶

45:22.120 --> 45:23.419
      - I love this song.

45:24.923 --> 45:27.090
        Come and dance
      with your mum, Max.

45:27.092 --> 45:28.291
- I don't want to fucking dance.

45:28.293 --> 45:29.392
     - Come on, Maxy, it's
     a fucking good song!

45:29.394 --> 45:30.827
      Let's go and dance!

45:30.829 --> 45:32.061
  It's a fucking good song!

45:32.063 --> 45:33.196
         Come on, Max!

45:33.198 --> 45:35.932
    - I don't want to dance.
           - Come on!

45:35.934 --> 45:38.201
       You'll dance with
      me, won't you, son?

45:38.203 --> 45:43.272
         ¶ On a deal ¶

45:47.746 --> 45:49.212
        ¶ Here we go ¶

45:49.214 --> 45:51.280
   - [Charlotte Voiceover]
 It's as if she wasn't there.

45:52.784 --> 45:53.416
         (car zooming)

45:53.418 --> 45:54.383
      On another planet.

45:56.888 --> 45:59.222
        (engine roaring)

45:59.224 --> 46:01.858
 He wanted to break her finger
    or slap her in the face

46:03.128 --> 46:04.260
  just to see if she felt it.

46:04.262 --> 46:06.095
        (engine roaring)

46:06.097 --> 46:07.263
      ¶ We made a deal ¶

46:07.265 --> 46:09.232
  ¶ Oh yeah we made a deal ¶

46:09.234 --> 46:11.334
        ¶ Oh my deal ¶

46:11.336 --> 46:12.969
    ¶ Yeah we had a deal ¶

46:12.971 --> 46:14.804
      - [Max Voiceover]
      I had a brother.

46:14.806 --> 46:15.505
        He's dead now.

46:17.408 --> 46:18.908
     I imagine I would've
         had more too

46:18.910 --> 46:20.476
      had mum not wised
      up to abortions.

46:22.280 --> 46:23.880
        What can I say?

46:23.882 --> 46:24.914
      She loves fucking.

46:26.050 --> 46:27.383
  She had no choice really.

46:27.385 --> 46:29.318
        She was raised a
        strict Catholic.

46:30.421 --> 46:32.021
      Every now and then
      mum would get drunk

46:32.023 --> 46:33.389
  and tell me about my dad.

46:34.359 --> 46:36.292
  The story always changed.

46:37.362 --> 46:38.261
         He was a cop.

46:39.130 --> 46:40.329
     Then he was a marine.

46:41.232 --> 46:43.366
     He was even a fucking
      secret agent once.

46:44.903 --> 46:46.269
I eventually tracked him down.

46:47.238 --> 46:49.038
He shot wild dogs for a living.

46:51.242 --> 46:52.809
At least he had a gun I guess.

46:53.878 --> 46:55.845
     (chilled rock music)

46:55.847 --> 46:59.081
     (cigarette crackling)

47:06.558 --> 47:07.523
        - Who's Mason?

47:09.828 --> 47:10.526
            - What?

47:11.963 --> 47:12.862
            - Mason.

47:16.067 --> 47:17.166
      I heard you talking
       with your mother

47:17.168 --> 47:18.401
  about someone called Mason.

47:21.272 --> 47:23.339
      (thunder rumbling)

47:23.341 --> 47:24.607
    Sounded like he's dead.

47:24.609 --> 47:26.309
      (glass shattering)

47:26.311 --> 47:29.512
    (nonchalant rock music)

47:37.989 --> 47:39.856
      (lighter flicking)

47:39.858 --> 47:40.556
          Who is he?

47:42.393 --> 47:43.359
         - My brother.

47:45.396 --> 47:47.163
      - [Charlotte] And?

47:50.268 --> 47:51.434
      - And he got sick.

47:54.305 --> 47:55.238
    - How did he get sick?

47:55.240 --> 47:58.307
      (voices whispering)

48:00.311 --> 48:01.377
      Did you poison him?

48:02.146 --> 48:03.412
          (smashing)

48:03.414 --> 48:06.249
      (voices whispering)

48:06.251 --> 48:07.617
        (haunting music)

48:07.619 --> 48:10.119
      (fire crackling)
      (people laughing)

48:10.121 --> 48:13.256
     (relaxed rock music)

48:19.430 --> 48:22.265
       - [Max] He died
     slowly and painfully

48:22.267 --> 48:23.232
        over six years.

48:23.234 --> 48:26.235
      (thunder rumbling)

48:27.372 --> 48:28.337
      - When did he die?

48:29.574 --> 48:30.406
    - What does it matter?

48:30.408 --> 48:31.440
            - When?

48:31.442 --> 48:32.341
          - Recently.

48:34.445 --> 48:36.078
      - So that's why you
       never came clean.

48:37.382 --> 48:38.347
  You had to look after him.

48:38.349 --> 48:41.183
        (fire roaring)

48:44.522 --> 48:47.523
      (thunder rumbling)

48:59.337 --> 49:00.569
- [Charlotte Voiceover] I like
  to think that's the reason

49:00.571 --> 49:02.438
      why Max never came
       clean about mum.

49:07.512 --> 49:08.377
  He never said that though.

49:12.483 --> 49:13.582
        I wish he had.

49:14.619 --> 49:17.453
        (fire roaring)

49:23.394 --> 49:25.528
  - Can I tell you a story?

49:27.732 --> 49:29.632
      (thunder rumbling)

49:29.634 --> 49:33.002
     (television zapping)

49:36.674 --> 49:39.442
         (scary music)

49:44.449 --> 49:47.183
  - [Woman On TV] Richard, do
you think the sheriff is right,

49:47.185 --> 49:50.152
  that the same person that
   killed Bud killed Tom?

49:50.154 --> 49:51.754
    - [Man On TV] Not much.

49:51.756 --> 49:54.557
    If it's a person at all.

49:54.559 --> 49:57.360
        (mystical music)

49:58.396 --> 50:00.396
         (phone rings)

50:00.398 --> 50:01.764
      - Charlotte, where
      the fuck are you?

50:01.766 --> 50:03.632
    - [Max] That's no way to
    speak to your daughter.

50:03.634 --> 50:05.101
 - What have you done to her?

50:05.103 --> 50:06.435
     - [Max] Don't panic,
     dad, she's sleeping.

50:06.437 --> 50:07.470
    Now what's the problem?

50:07.472 --> 50:08.404
      - Don't play dumb.

50:08.406 --> 50:11.007
The cops have your fingerprints!

50:11.009 --> 50:12.108
    They were on the inside
      of a television set

50:12.110 --> 50:13.709
    inside the motel room!

50:13.711 --> 50:15.611
    You opened it up to fix
  the reception or something.

50:15.613 --> 50:18.481
   The point is the owner
  still has the fucking TV!

50:20.084 --> 50:21.684
        Your prints on
     record for anything?

50:25.423 --> 50:26.622
            - Yes.

50:26.624 --> 50:28.424
    I got caught with weed
    when I was a teenager.

50:28.426 --> 50:29.592
       - Why didn't you
      tell me about this?

50:29.594 --> 50:31.060
    Now everything's fucked!

50:33.064 --> 50:35.131
Not gonna say sorry this time?

50:35.133 --> 50:37.366
  (laughs) That's a change.

50:37.368 --> 50:38.567
 Anyway, this is not over yet.

50:38.569 --> 50:40.436
 I'll think of something new.

50:40.438 --> 50:42.571
       We've just got a
     ticking clock is all.

50:44.475 --> 50:47.510
  - I'm coming to kill you.

50:47.512 --> 50:48.577
            - What?

50:51.416 --> 50:53.482
  - I'm coming to kill you.

50:53.484 --> 50:55.484
I've seen the newspaper articles

50:55.486 --> 50:57.486
and I know that you're on to me,

50:57.488 --> 50:59.422
      so I'm coming to
      town to kill you.

51:00.491 --> 51:01.424
      You have a dream.

51:01.426 --> 51:02.625
 Juliette tells you I'm coming

51:02.627 --> 51:04.493
       and that you'll
      be waiting for me.

51:04.495 --> 51:06.562
    - [Edmund] And I disable
      you in my own house.

51:06.564 --> 51:07.797
     - And then I confess,

51:07.799 --> 51:09.298
      you find the plates
       to seal the deal.

51:09.300 --> 51:10.299
      - [Edmund] And then

51:11.302 --> 51:13.502
    you're finally forgiven.

51:13.504 --> 51:14.403
             - No.

51:16.107 --> 51:17.139
    You forgive Charlotte.

51:17.141 --> 51:20.109
      (mysterious music)

51:22.113 --> 51:23.546
 - What are you talking about?

51:23.548 --> 51:25.614
     - [Max] You know what
      I'm talking about.

51:27.285 --> 51:30.152
       You blame her for
     the accident, not me.

51:32.590 --> 51:34.356
You're never to see her again.

51:35.359 --> 51:36.559
          She's free.

51:36.561 --> 51:39.228
     - You are a cold son
     of a bitch after all.

51:39.230 --> 51:40.596
  - [Max] Do we have a deal?

51:43.835 --> 51:44.767
      - Any other terms?

51:45.636 --> 51:47.603
    - [Max] You do it now.

51:47.605 --> 51:50.206
        (spooky music)

51:55.179 --> 51:55.811
    - [Charlotte Voiceover]
      Something washed up

51:55.813 --> 51:56.879
      on the shore once.

51:58.749 --> 52:01.117
      It didn't look like
    anything I'd ever seen.

52:02.587 --> 52:04.687
 It was all spikes and teeth.

52:06.491 --> 52:09.125
  I couldn't tell if it was
  that way to attack things

52:10.528 --> 52:11.760
     or to protect itself.

52:13.764 --> 52:14.897
     I would've killed it,

52:16.234 --> 52:17.766
      but I didn't want
      to get that close.

52:20.771 --> 52:22.271
      I just walked away.

52:23.875 --> 52:25.407
     Hoping it would die.

52:25.409 --> 52:28.477
      (upbeat surf music)

52:31.816 --> 52:32.715
          - You okay?

52:34.652 --> 52:35.651
          - I'm fine.

52:38.289 --> 52:40.556
